return array(
'title'=>'Heliogeophysical forecast center established in Beijing Observatory',
'class'=>0,
'cont'=>', Solar-terrestrial physics Prediction Center in Beijing Observatory was established on March 3, 1992 (Renshen first month&#39;s Eve). State Science and Technology Commission and the Chinese Academy of Sciences approved the establishment of the World alarm center heliogeophysical, Prediction Center in <br> 1991. March 3rd, 1992 solar-terrestrial physics Prediction Center was established in Beijing Observatory. Solar-terrestrial physics Prediction Center (RWC-Beijing) consists of four sub-centers: Geophysical Forecast Center, Space Center for Environmental Prediction, the Forecast Center of the ionosphere and solar activity forecasting center, headquartered in Beijing, the Hong Kong Observatory. According to the requirements of the International Space Environment Service Organization in 2000, changed its name to China Regional Warning Center (RWC-China), its purpose is: to improve solar-terrestrial physics forecast level, expanding the scope of services, and to promote the study of the Sun-Earth space environment and forecast, to carry out day terrestrial physics research and forecasting of domestic and international cooperation and exchanges with other international regional warning centers for the rapid exchange of information in order to obtain information and forecasts of the global solar-terrestrial physics services in the region. (History TodayOnHistory.com) <br>'
